# __PROJECT_NAME__

An MCP server with embedded Meter billing, running on **Cloudflare Workers**.
Each tool call reserves prepaid credits, runs, then commits the actual price; an
insufficient balance returns `payment_required` instead of running for free.

## Run it locally

```bash
npm run dev
```

`wrangler dev` serves on `http://localhost:8787/mcp` and reads the service API
key from `.dev.vars`. In another terminal, call a tool through the Meter CLI
(the caller identifies the buyer with an `x-customer-id` header, which
`meter call` sends as `--customer`):

```bash
meter call echo --url http://localhost:8787/mcp --args '{"text":"hi"}'
```

Then watch the usage events land in your Meter service:

```bash
meter events tail
```

## Deploy

The service API key is a secret, so it lives in `.dev.vars` (gitignored) for
local dev and in Wrangler's secret store for production — never in
`wrangler.jsonc`:

```bash
npx wrangler secret put METER_SERVICE_API_KEY   # paste the key from .dev.vars
npm run deploy
```

`wrangler.jsonc` already carries the non-secret `METER_API_URL` and
`METER_SERVICE_ID` as plain vars.

## Switching to the Meter gateway

The commands above call this server directly. To put Meter's hosted gateway in
front of it — so credit checks, auto-recharge, and customer auth run at the
edge instead of in this Worker — deploy it, then point your service's
integration at its URL:

```bash
meter integration update --upstream-url <deployed URL> --gateway-enabled true
```

Callers then hit the gateway URL, and Meter forwards paid, authenticated
requests upstream to this Worker.
